President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has sent a notice to the Federal Register stating that the national emergency with respect to harmful foreign activities of the Russian government will continue beyond April 15, 2023. These activities include efforts to undermine democratic elections, engage in cyber-enabled attacks, use corruption to influence foreign governments, target dissidents or journalists, undermine security in important regions, and violate international law. The President has determined that these activities pose a significant threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States.